---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navigation from "../../components/Navigation.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="Why I Write in Public">
  <Navigation />

  <main id="main-content" class="flex-1 max-w-[68ch] mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 flex flex-col gap-12 font-sans">
    
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <div class="flex gap-2 text-xs text-[#71717A] font-mono">
        <span>Essay</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>May 2025</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-display font-medium text-[#FAFAFA] tracking-tight leading-tight">
        Why I Write in Public
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] italic">
        "This website isn't a record of expertise. It's a record of progress."
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-8 text-[#FAFAFA] text-base leading-[1.7] tracking-tight font-normal">
      <p>
        Writing technical explanations is easy when you are not publishing them.
        In private journals, you can skip over details and gloss over edge cases.
        Writing in public removes this shortcuts.
        Knowing that other engineers might read your notes forces absolute precision.
      </p>
      
      <p>
        Publishing also helps you deal with the fear of being wrong.
        Every developer makes mistakes, chooses incorrect architectures, or over-engineers early database schemas.
        By documenting these mistakes openly, you normalize failure as the primary driver of learning.
      </p>

      <p>
        I do not write because I have mastered systems.
        I write because it is the process through which I analyze and understand them.
        Making drafts public creates a feedback loop that sharpens engineering fundamentals.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Article Footer -->
    <footer class="flex flex-col gap-8 border-t border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pt-12 mt-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8 text-sm">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <h4 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-medium">Further Reading</h4>
          <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2">
            <li>
              <a href="/writing/why-i-started-writing" class="text-[#2563EB] hover:underline">
                Why I Started Writing
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
